cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with text classification for early risk detection on social media, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with data streams and incremental learning, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for identifying relevant data, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with ethical considerations and justifying decisions, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
